# Rust / Cargo
#
# Keep Cargo.lock in — mergeFox is a **binary application**, not a
# library, and the lockfile is what lets CI / release builds reproduce
# the exact dependency tree. Only `target/` and rustfmt backups are out.
/target
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# Claude Code — local session state (agent settings, worktrees, caches)
# lives under `.claude/`. Personal to each developer; never pushed.
.claude/

# Claude Agent SDK / scheduled tasks that some versions drop in-repo
.claude/scheduled-tasks/

# Profiling artefacts generated by MERGEFOX_PROFILE_FRAMES / _DIFF when
# the user redirects stderr to a file. Not code, not reproducible, out.
/*.profile
*.profile.log
mergefox-profile*.log

# Crash / panic dump files eframe can write on shutdown
crash.log
panic.log

# IDE / editor
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
# Vim / emacs swap + backup
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS metadata — match recursively so nested .DS_Store inside src/ etc.
# are ignored too. The previous `.DS_Store` (root-only) pattern let
# `src/.DS_Store` leak in.
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Environment / secrets — belt-and-suspenders over our OS-keychain
# storage. If anyone ever drops a `.env` here by accident, it stops at
# the commit boundary.
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
!*.example.key
id_rsa
id_rsa.pub
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.pub

# OS-bundle build outputs (cargo-bundle / create-dmg / Inno Setup)
/release/
*.dmg
*.pkg
*.msi
*.exe.zip
/out/
